---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="How We Rank Schools — Methodology" description="How British Schools Asia ranks British curriculum schools across Asia.">
  <Header slot="header" />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="bsa-container">
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <p class="label mb-4">Methodology</p>
        <h1 class="mb-8">How We Rank Schools</h1>

        <div class="space-y-6 font-body text-black/70 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            Our research team and panel of industry experts maintain a ranked index of British curriculum schools across Asia. Rankings reflect a combination of detailed school analysis and direct community feedback.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl mt-10 mb-4 text-black">Independent research</h2>
          <p>
            Every school in the index is reviewed by our research team against a consistent set of criteria covering academic offer, facilities, staffing, leadership, and overall investment in the student experience. Our experts draw on years of experience working with international schools across the region.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl mt-10 mb-4 text-black">Parent and community feedback</h2>
          <p>
            Independent research alone does not tell the full story. Our editorial team gathers feedback from parents, alumni, and the wider school community to ensure rankings reflect lived experience as well as institutional standing. Schools with persistent concerns raised by the community may receive a downward adjustment in the rankings.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl mt-10 mb-4 text-black">Editorial reviews</h2>
          <p>
            We publish editorial reviews for schools where we have sufficient information to form a view. Where our research is still underway, the school profile displays factual information only.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl mt-10 mb-4 text-black">What the index does not do</h2>
          <p>
            This is not a league table of exam results. Academic outcomes may be incorporated in future editions. No school can pay to be ranked, promoted, or removed.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-12">
          <a href="/rankings" class="btn-ghost-dark">View Rankings</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</BaseLayout>
